/","url_meta":{"origin":33174,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Festivals of ignorance replaced by two Eids","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 23, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, arrived in Medina during two days which they were celebrating. The Prophet said, \u201cWhat are these two days?\u201d They said, \u201cWe would celebrate these two days in the time of ignorance.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, Allah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19612,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/no-adhan-eid-nawafil-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":33174,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Eid: No call to prayer for Eid, voluntary prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Samurah reported: I performed the Eid prayers with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, more than once, without announcing the two calls to prayer. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 887 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cThis is acted upon by the scholars among\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15674,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/14\/no-fasting-eid-fitr-adha-tashriq\/","url_meta":{"origin":33174,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Eids: Days of Eid are celebrations, not for fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 14, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"'Uqbah ibn 'Amir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe day of Arafat, the day of sacrifice, and the three following days of al-Tashriq\u00a0are celebrations for the people of Islam. They are days of eating and drinking.\u201d Al-Tirmidhi said, \"The people of knowledge acted\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19589,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/seven-five-takbir-salat-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":33174,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Seven and five Takbir in Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amr ibn 'Awf reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would pronounce takbir during the Eid prayer seven times before the recitation in the first cycle, and five times before the recitation in the second cycle. Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cThis tradition is acted upon by some of the people\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5037,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/12\/prophet-dates-eid-al-fitr\/","url_meta":{"origin":33174,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Eid: The Prophet eats dates before Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 12, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and bless